  "text": "When V is a complex line bundle, we write D F instead of D F,E . For the sub-Dirac operator D F we will calculate the bosonic part of the spectral action. It is defined to be the number of eigenvalues of D F in the interval [−∧, ∧] with ∧ ∈ R + . As in [CITATION_1] , it is expressed as",
